1
00:00:00,167 --> 00:00:01,700
My name is Ahmad Khaled Ahmad

2
00:00:02,458 --> 00:00:04,613
I was born in the Housh al-Biaa neighborhood

3
00:00:04,624 --> 00:00:06,424
Which they also call Housh al-Kanaes [Courtyard of the Churches]

4
00:00:07,058 --> 00:00:11,190
I work as a porter for wooden items

5
00:00:11,957 --> 00:00:14,323
And I work as a porter for lumber

6
00:00:15,083 --> 00:00:17,867
I am a resident of this neighborhood

7
00:00:18,538 --> 00:00:20,670
I was born in 1975

8
00:00:20,921 --> 00:00:22,287
I am 48 years old

9
00:00:22,909 --> 00:00:26,342
I grew up and was raised in this neighborhood

10
00:00:28,397 --> 00:00:30,752
Interviewer: What year did you first enter this church?

11
00:00:31,944 --> 00:00:39,561
I came to this church when I was about 13 or 14 years old

12
00:00:40,201 --> 00:00:44,112
In 1983 or 1982

13
00:00:44,369 --> 00:00:45,969
I entered this church

14
00:00:46,188 --> 00:00:48,110
I ate and drank here

15
00:00:48,456 --> 00:00:52,911
And I joined our Christian brothers in their occasions

16
00:00:53,067 --> 00:00:56,117
When their Sunday prayers came, we would come with them

17
00:00:56,428 --> 00:00:58,928
We accompanied them and sat in the church

18
00:00:59,820 --> 00:01:02,336
We shook hands and talked with them

19
00:01:02,555 --> 00:01:05,610
They are good people, beyond description

20
00:01:05,707 --> 00:01:08,674
Their essence is of gold, and I salute them from here

21
00:01:09,058 --> 00:01:11,484
I swear they are people I hold above me, the Christians

22
00:01:11,695 --> 00:01:15,798
Interviewer: Ahmad, your first entry into this church, for what occasion was it?

23
00:01:16,453 --> 00:01:22,017
What was it for, and what ritual or event did you come to attend?

24
00:01:22,286 --> 00:01:27,163
Interviewer: What do you remember?
Witness: What I remember was every Sunday

25
00:01:27,428 --> 00:01:31,616
On the occasion of their prayer, as we have
Friday prayers, they had Sunday prayers

26
00:01:31,822 --> 00:01:34,454
This ritual was constant in their faith

27
00:01:34,908 --> 00:01:36,452
I was with them every Sunday

28
00:01:36,508 --> 00:01:41,206
By God, we spent all our time in the church courtyard

29
00:01:41,403 --> 00:01:45,336
We would play and move from one
church to another, we were part of them

30
00:01:45,586 --> 00:01:48,208
We were part of them, to the point I knew all these churches well

31
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:51,065
There were six churches in this area

32
00:01:51,288 --> 00:01:52,554
They called it Housh al-Biaa

33
00:01:52,858 --> 00:01:55,775
I entered all the churches

34
00:01:55,797 --> 00:01:58,841
And I joined them in religious rituals

35
00:01:59,245 --> 00:02:00,245
Yes

36
00:02:00,601 --> 00:02:04,400
Interviewer: I want to ask you, do you know Old Mosul?

37
00:02:04,667 --> 00:02:06,945
Did you visit it regularly?

38
00:02:07,658 --> 00:02:12,279
And have you visited other churches in this neighborhood?

39
00:02:12,572 --> 00:02:14,038
I would like you to share these details

40
00:02:14,083 --> 00:02:17,621
Witness: Yes, we went to a place

41
00:02:17,646 --> 00:02:19,021
They called it Eid al-Deir

42
00:02:19,066 --> 00:02:23,222
Eid al-Deir was held at a site in the Arabi neighborhood

43
00:02:23,311 --> 00:02:25,511
The church was Mar Gorgis

44
00:02:25,992 --> 00:02:30,518
This ritual lasted for a month in the spring

45
00:02:30,751 --> 00:02:33,151
It was held in the fourth month

46
00:02:33,460 --> 00:02:35,846
We would go, join them, and find a place

47
00:02:36,135 --> 00:02:38,368
From early morning, five a.m.

48
00:02:38,558 --> 00:02:40,002
Just to secure a spot

49
00:02:40,361 --> 00:02:42,694
It was a communal meal as well as a religious ritual

50
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:46,327
That we shared with our Christian brothers, at Mar Gorgis

51
00:02:46,539 --> 00:02:49,005
We entered the church and prayed with them

52
00:02:49,353 --> 00:02:50,586
And supported them

53
00:02:50,776 --> 00:02:53,309
We brought dolma with us and sat on a hill beside it

54
00:02:53,488 --> 00:02:54,977
And their cemetery was there

55
00:02:55,242 --> 00:02:57,297
We joined them in all of this

56
00:02:57,497 --> 00:02:59,708
Especially in this ritual, and another ritual

57
00:02:59,842 --> 00:03:01,775
Which was held at al-Tahira Church

58
00:03:02,019 --> 00:03:03,886
Located near Bash Tapia

59
00:03:04,318 --> 00:03:06,751
Al-Tahira Church, there are two called al-Tahira

60
00:03:06,776 --> 00:03:08,198
This one and the other

61
00:03:08,410 --> 00:03:13,499
That one’s ritual was held on March 21

62
00:03:13,602 --> 00:03:15,042
The same as Nowruz

63
00:03:15,247 --> 00:03:16,613
Which fell on that day

64
00:03:16,635 --> 00:03:18,157
We joined them in their ritual

65
00:03:18,313 --> 00:03:22,313
With a picnic, along with all the Christians living in Kurdistan

66
00:03:22,490 --> 00:03:24,856
They came for this ritual, we joined and rejoiced

67
00:03:25,039 --> 00:03:27,638
And we sat at an outdoor table

68
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:30,406
We climbed Bash Tapia with dolma and kibbeh with us

69
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:32,684
And the Christians brought tabboulleh

70
00:03:32,709 --> 00:03:35,706
A favorite dish for them, as dolma and kibbeh are for us

71
00:03:35,907 --> 00:03:37,151
They had tabboulleh

72
00:03:37,163 --> 00:03:40,980
Tabbouleh is indescribable, even now I crave it, it was delicious

73
00:03:41,069 --> 00:03:42,302
Its taste is still in my mouth

74
00:03:42,790 --> 00:03:46,234
Interviewer: Did you visit the churches near this church?

75
00:03:46,259 --> 00:03:48,147
Witness: Yes, I visited them

76
00:03:48,167 --> 00:03:51,974
Even the people who lived there

77
00:03:52,263 --> 00:03:54,930
They were also Christians and part of the church

78
00:03:54,963 --> 00:03:57,679
We sat with them in the church and in their homes

79
00:03:57,708 --> 00:04:00,368
We shared their food and drink and played with their kids

80
00:04:00,618 --> 00:04:02,240
Church by church, I knew them

81
00:04:02,449 --> 00:04:04,160
Every room in every church, I knew them

82
00:04:04,185 --> 00:04:08,426
I knew all the rituals because I joined them so often

83
00:04:08,580 --> 00:04:13,446
Interviewer: Ahmad, as a Muslim from Mosul

84
00:04:13,568 --> 00:04:19,336
What do these memories with our Christian brothers—our partners—mean to you?

85
00:04:19,409 --> 00:04:24,130
Witness: They truly are our partners, they are sincere people

86
00:04:24,305 --> 00:04:25,305
Good people

87
00:04:25,556 --> 00:04:27,222
No need to explain, let me give an example

88
00:04:27,835 --> 00:04:29,979
They came when Ramadan arrived

89
00:04:30,430 --> 00:04:33,385
Because they were so kind and friendly

90
00:04:33,872 --> 00:04:36,627
There was no difference in religion, we were one, God knows

91
00:04:36,652 --> 00:04:38,605
They worshiped God and we worshiped God

92
00:04:38,828 --> 00:04:40,833
Our religion was one, us and them

93
00:04:41,187 --> 00:04:43,553
Faithful, kind, trustworthy neighbors

94
00:04:43,595 --> 00:04:47,650
True neighbors who respected rights in an indescribable way

95
00:04:47,716 --> 00:04:49,083
Every Ramadan

96
00:04:49,555 --> 00:04:51,254
They showed respect for Muslims

97
00:04:51,477 --> 00:04:52,710
They wore headscarves

98
00:04:53,277 --> 00:04:55,667
During our fasting, throughout Ramadan

99
00:04:55,945 --> 00:04:58,633
When they went out to clean, they wore a scarf

100
00:04:58,971 --> 00:05:01,337
Out of respect for our rituals and our Islamic faith

101
00:05:01,784 --> 00:05:05,606
At iftar, they brought us dates

102
00:05:05,701 --> 00:05:08,478
Whatever food they had, they shared it with us

103
00:05:08,593 --> 00:05:10,204
They came to our homes and knocked on the door

104
00:05:10,405 --> 00:05:13,449
They brought us dates, kibbeh, and tabbouni

105
00:05:13,682 --> 00:05:14,899
That was their food

106
00:05:15,121 --> 00:05:16,921
They never forgot us during Ramadan

107
00:05:17,187 --> 00:05:19,787
I thank them from here, they are always in my heart

108
00:05:19,955 --> 00:05:22,355
They cannot be forgotten, especially for these acts

109
00:05:22,933 --> 00:05:25,315
Anyone who shared that knows their value

110
00:05:25,571 --> 00:05:28,460
Christians are people worthy to keep in my eyes and above my head

111
00:05:28,549 --> 00:05:29,960
Of course, they are my heart and soul
